Bringing people together through coffee. 

Team Mills foundation has joined forces with an Australian cafe powerhouse to create Bluestone Lane Keriba Ged. A six week long, immersive experiential learning opportunity in hospitality and business for emerging professionals and leaders.

Applications are now being accepted for the Bluestone Lane Keriba Ged Program! “Keriba”, meaning “Our” and “Ged” meaning “Home” or “Place”, is a unique program that will see Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples have the opportunity to develop premium business and hospitality skills at Bluestone Lane locations in the United States. 

Accepting its first cohort into New York City in 2023, the Keriba Ged program will open up pathways to success for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples to live and train abroad, enabling them to learn and develop valuable leadership, project management, networking, financial, communication and customer service skills. Link in bio to find out more information.💙

WE ARE LAUNCHING TOMORROW!! 

I can’t believe the day is finally here. After every ounce of passion being poured into something I truly love and believe in, I am extremely excited to be revealing the recreation of my island lifestyle brand - @strait.thelabel 

Starting this journey 6 years ago was nerve racking but I loved it so much I took the leap. I have learned so much over time in this space and now to see it evolve into an actual label is still mind blowing. I am so grateful for my team and everything we have accomplished already because I love what I do with the people I love and that's what makes me live for these moments. 

Can't wait to share it with you all. 

Launch and drop of our newest collection tomorrow! 5.21

Welcome to strait. the label @strait.thelabel 

An island lifestyle brand, created, designed and powered by island women. For all women, wherever they may be in the world.

At the heart of @strait.thelabel is an affinity with land, culture and sea. @strait.thelabel embodies the island woman. She who shares a deep connection with nature – admiring and enjoying its beauty in its simplest, yet richest form.

Each collection captures the true essence of island life. Our pieces act as daily reminders of a life to be treasured in the here & now, or perhaps a window to the life we aspire to lead. And with a conscious lifestyle at the heart of everything we do, all our collections remain small scale.

We believe we are the artists of our own lives, each day an expression of who we really are. We create opportunity for an individual to connect, in their own way, to natural island elements. To stop, take a breath and cherish the moment.

At strait, island life is our way of life. That’s what we call a ‘strait. state of mind.’

Our Isle collection invokes the feeling of bliss and comfort with prints inspired by island blooms across the Pacific, each stitch and seam hugging like its fluid waters. Life slows down in our statement pieces, reminding you to stay in the present moment and revel in the day to day, forever in a strait. state of mind.

From the bottom of my heart, I want to thank all the beautiful island women who created, designed and powered this magnificent brand to life. I’m truly grateful  for you all. Mahalo and Esso. Love you girls.
